Description: Handle and rim sherd of East Greek painted grey ware pottery closed vessel, probably a trefoil oinochoe, with thickened lip and root of twisted handle; pale grey fabric with mica inclusions; dark grey slip on interior and exterior surface; traces of red paint on interior surface.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.088)
